It is possible to include dynamic explanatory variables through the
ExpVarRasterList function, by ensuring the names of the dynamic raster
maps follow a certain naming convention. This is explained in the lulcc
manual
(https://cran.r-project.org/web/packages/lulcc/lulcc.pdf). Briefly, your
maps should be named something like:

ef_1_0.tif, ef_1_1.tif, ef_1_2.tif, ef_1_3.tif...

The first number differentiates the variable from other explanatory
variables (e.g. population from elevation), and the second number
indicates the time for which the variable is relevant (population at
time 0, 1, 2, 3...).

I hope this is clear - do let me know if not.

Thanks,
Simon

